AIE: PCI-DSS: Audit Log Write Failure Alert Rule
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This AIE Rule alerts on the occurrence of audit log write failures in direct support of PCI-DSS Controls: 10.2.6

CommonEvent.Name: AIE: NIST 800-53 : Failed Audit Log Write Rule
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This AIE Rule provides details on audit log write failures.

CommonEvent.Name: AIE: GPG-13 : Failed Audit Log Write Rule
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This AIE Rule directly supports GPG-13 control PMC10.1 by alerting on all audit log write failures.

CommonEvent.Name: AIE: CSF: Failed Audit Log Write Rule
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This AIE Rule provides details on audit log write failures.

CommonEvent.Name: AIE: GPG-13: Rejected Connection to Network
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This Rule creates an event and alerts on failed attempts to connect equipment to protected network attachment points at the boundary to supplement testing of GPG-13 control PMC6.6 [Alert B]

CommonEvent.Name: AIE: ISO-27001: Rejected Connection to Network
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This Rule creates an event and alerts on failed attempts to connect equipment to protected network attachment points at the network perimeter and is specifically concerned with 802.1x port security on switches.

CommonEvent.Name: AIE: MAS: Audit Log Write Failure Alert
CommonEvent.ShortDesc: AIE: This AIE Rule alerts on the occurrence of audit log write failures.
